## 2. USER FLOWS

### 2.1 Primary Personas

**P1: Potential Buyer (Construction Company Owner/Manager)**
- Goal: Evaluate machines for purchase/rental, compare specs, request quote
- Pain point: Needs confidence in after-sales support
- Device: Desktop (research) → Mobile (share/forward)

**P2: Service Requester (Site Manager/Equipment Operator)**
- Goal: Get machine repaired FAST, ideally on-site
- Pain point: Downtime costs money; needs 24/7 availability
- Device: Mobile (urgent, on-site calls)

**P3: Spare Parts Purchaser (Procurement/Mechanic)**
- Goal: Find part number, check availability, order quickly
- Pain point: Uncertainty if part is in stock
- Device: Desktop (lookup) → Mobile (call to confirm)

**P4: Referral/Partner (Putzmeister HQ, other dealers)**
- Goal: Verify legitimacy, check company standing
- Pain point: Needs professional presentation
- Device: Desktop

