## 5. MOBILE UX STRATEGY

### 5.1 Mobile-First ≠ Mobile-Only

This is a B2B industrial site. **Primary research happens on desktop.** Primary **emergency contacts happen on mobile.** The mobile experience must serve both modes excellently.

### 5.2 Mobile-Specific Patterns

#### A. Thumb Zone Optimization
```
┌─────────────────────┐
│  Header (70px)      │  <- Logo left, hamburger right
├─────────────────────┤
│                     │
│    Content Area     │
│                     │
├─────────────────────┤
│  Emergency FAB      │  <- Bottom-right, 56px, red, thumb reachable
│  (only if scrolled) │
├─────────────────────┤
│  Bottom CTA Bar     │  <- "Обадете се" fixed, 48px height, hides at footer
│  (below fold only)  │
└─────────────────────┘
```

#### B. Touch Targets
- All interactive elements: minimum 48×48dp (Apple HIG) / 44×44dp (Material)
- Nav links in mobile menu: 56px height minimum
- Cards: entire card is tap target (not just title)
- Form inputs: 56px height, 16px font size (prevents iOS zoom)

#### C. Swipe Gestures
- Machine carousel: horizontal swipe with momentum scroll
- Mobile menu: swipe right to close
- Image gallery: swipe between images
- Testimonials: swipe horizontally (pause marquee)

#### D. Sticky Behaviors
- **Header**: Fixed, shrinks from 70px to 56px after 100px scroll
- **Bottom CTA bar**: Appears after scrolling past hero, hides when near footer
- **Emergency FAB**: Appears after 200px scroll, pulses for attention
- **Filter bar** (machines page): Sticky below shrunken header

#### E. Form Experience
- Inputs have top-aligned labels (not placeholders that disappear)
- Keyboard types: `tel` for phone, `email` for email
- Submit button fixed at bottom of viewport while form is focused
- Autocomplete attributes on all fields
- Success state: full-screen confirmation with confetti disabled (industrial restraint)

#### F. Image Loading
- Hero: eager load, LQIP (low-quality image placeholder) blur-up
- All others: lazy loading with skeleton placeholder
- Skeleton: dark gray pulse animation, matches card dimensions

#### G. Performance Budget (Mobile)
- First Contentful Paint: < 1.5s
- Largest Contentful Paint: < 2.5s
- Time to Interactive: < 3.5s
- Total page weight: < 1.5MB per route
- No layout shift: images have explicit width/height attributes

### 5.3 Mobile vs Desktop Differentiation

| Feature | Desktop | Mobile |
|---------|---------|--------|
| Hero | Video background, side-by-side text layout | Static optimized image, stacked text, smaller typography |
| Navigation | Horizontal links + MegaMenu dropdowns | Full-screen overlay, grouped categories |
| Machine cards | 3-column grid with hover lift | 1-column stack, tap to view, no hover state |
| Comparison tool | Inline checkbox + fixed bottom bar | Same, but modal is full-screen |
| Stats counters | 4-column layout | 2x2 grid, counters still animate |
| Coverage map | SVG with hover regions | SVG static, tap region to show tooltip |
| Testimonials | Marquee auto-scroll | Swipeable carousel, 1 card visible |
| Forms | Side-by-side fields | Stacked, full-width |
| Gallery | Thumbnail sidebar + main | Swipeable, thumbnail dots below |
| CTA placement | Inline within content | Fixed bottom bar + emergency FAB |

