```

### 9.2 Animation Implementation Stack

| Effect | Technology | Fallback |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| Scroll-triggered reveals | IntersectionObserver + CSS transitions | No animation, content visible immediately |
| Counters | Custom hook `useCountUp(target, duration)` | Show final number immediately |
| Parallax | CSS `transform: translateY(calc(var(--scroll) * 0.3))` via JS rAF throttled to 60fps | Static positioning |
| Marquee | CSS animation + duplicated content | Static grid |
| SVG line draw | CSS `stroke-dashoffset` transition | Solid line, no draw |
| Page transitions | React Router + CSS transition group | Instant navigation |
| Image zoom | CSS transform scale | No zoom |

### 9.3 Performance Rules

```
1. Hero image: preload, <link rel="preload"> in HTML
2. Lazy load everything below fold: IntersectionObserver + dynamic import
3. CSS: Single file, no unused selectors (purge if needed)
4. Fonts: Preconnect to Google Fonts CDN; font-display: swap
5. Images: WebP with JPEG fallback; explicit width/height
6. Animations: Use transform/opacity only (GPU composited)
7. Debounce scroll handlers to 16ms (60fps)
8. No layout thrashing: Read layout values, then write styles
```

### 9.4 Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

```
• Color contrast: Yellow #f9c500 on black = 10.8:1 ✓
• Red #cc2936 on white = 4.6:1 — needs adjustment or dark background
• Focus states: All interactive elements have visible 2px yellow outline
• Skip link: "Skip to main content" first focusable element
• ARIA labels: Icons, buttons, form errors
• Screen reader: Section headings use proper h1→h6 hierarchy
• Reduced motion: Respected via media query
• Touch targets: 48×48px minimum
• Form errors: Inline with `aria-describedby` linking to error text
```

